flowRoot.flowPara: Il y a 50 ans, Valentina Terechkova devenait la 1ère femme dans l’espace. La cosmonaute soviétique reste à ce jour la seule femme et la plus jeune à avoir effectué un vol spatial en solo.
Emission JT 20H - Production producteur ou co-producteur Sovexport film - Générique journaliste Zitrone, Léon

Depuis Moscou, entouré par les membres du gouvernement, le premier secrétaire du Parti communiste d'Union soviétique Nikita KHROUCHTCHEV s'entretient au téléphone avec la cosmonaute Valentina TERECHKOVA,
en orbite dans l'espace autour de la Terre à bord de la capsule Vostok 6,

Microtrottoir à Paris à propos de la première femme dans l'espace, Valentina Terechkova.Interviews de passants, une dame assez âgée trouve l'exploit de Valentina Terechkova extraordinaire, une jeune fille aimerait accomplir le même exploit mais une autre femme trouve que c'est uniquement la place des hommes. Une infirmière pense que cela n'a rien d'extraordinaire car les femmes sont aussi fortes que les hommes. Un homme regrette que ce soit une russe et pas une française.

flowRoot.flowPara: The Bad Habits were a locally-based Manchester band performing in the mid-1980s. The alternative scene in Manchester was beginning to take off at around this time after Factory records and the Hacienda had been set up. Bands like the Fall were influential but only a few women musicians were involved. We were one of only two or three women’s bands in Manchester at this time.

Diane has deposited a full set of her photos taken at the conference with the Feminist Archive North. Photos and Spare Rib article originally kindly donated by Jenny Clegg.

Het is mijn gewoonte niet, romans te schrijven, of zulke dingen, en het heeft dan ook lang geduurd, voor ik er toe overging een paar riem papier extra te bestellen, en het werk aan te vangen, dat gij, lieve lezer, zoâven in de hand hebt genomen, en dat ge lezen moet als ge makelaar in koffie zijt, of als ge wat anders zijt. Niet alleen dat ik nooit iets schreef wat naar een roman geleek, maar ik houd er zelfs niet van, iets dergelijks te lezen, omdat ik een man van zaken ben.

The Bad Habits were a locally-based Manchester band performing in the mid-1980s. The alternative scene in Manchester was beginning to take off at around this time after Factory records and the Hacienda had been set up. Bands like the Fall were influential but only a few women musicians were involved. We were one of only two or three women’s bands in Manchester at this time.

Sa réflexion sur la mondialisation, les "géographies imaginaires et matérielles du monde capitaliste avancé", passe également par une enquête ininterrompue sur l'espace maritime; d'abord avec la production des livres et des expositions rassemblées sous le titre Fish Story (1989-95), forme hybride comprenant "une sorte d'essai expérimental en mots et en images, en référence à la tradition d'Orwell, ou bien de James Agee-Walker Evans.

flowRoot.flowPara: Chiara Fumai, born in 1978 in Rome, lives in Milan. | Why am I dressed like this? Am I going to get married? Am I going to perform? | I am going to tell you a bit about the un-work I presented at Documenta Last year, a freak show of one hundred days | in the park, was playing a bit about the witch and repression | Let's spit on Hegel and I say I | Two texts of Carla Lonzi. | Feminism as a daemon and also this way of how culture perceives an idea that i contradictory but that is not contradictory. A thought from the double. That is not logocentric. | Extrait : The Spell | Then there was a performance act. A freak showed I ran for one hundred days. | “Ich verkörpere die Freaks der Gegenwart und Zukunft. Meine Kunst ist eine Freakshow. Ich brauche eine Gestalt, in die ich schlüpfen kann, aber es geht mir nicht um historische Vorbilder. Meine Performance ist ganz und gar heutig.”| This Zaluma ... was called the Star of the East, which means Lucifer | She was a perfomer of the Barnum Museum, she has never been famous, she was a B character. | I was very fascinated by the fact that she never spoke on the stage | How many feminists are in this room? | Who is not fully feminist? | Do you know who said that ideology is also my adventure? | Adventure and ideology are incompatible | I am my own adventure | One day of depression one year of depression one hundred years of depression | I discard ideology and I no longer know anything | Losing my way is my proof | I no longer have a glamourous moment at my disposition | | I lose attractiveness | But you will not find an anchor-point in me! | Who said that emancipation has been unmasked ? | You court me now because you fear that I will be the interlocutor with the world that you | You wait for identity from me and cannot make up your own. | You were given an identity by man and cannot give it up. | You burden me with your conflict and are hostile to me | You assault my integrity | You would like to put me on a pedestal | You would like to keep me under your guardianship | I distance myself and you do not forgive me | You do not know who I am and you make yourself my mediator. | What I have to say I will say on my own | Who said that you helped my cause? | I helped your career | But by appearing I spoiled your party | Provocation is a gesture of attachment | You force me to be present at painful revenges on a note of defiance | You celebrate a myth that fell with me | Who said that culture is a sublime goal ? | It is the sublime goal of self-destruction | | In acquiring culture you have complied unreservedly with a request that excludes you | You have wanted to participate without existing on your own | Ultimately you are unrecognizable | And while this has been happening, you have sufferred from a feeling of inadequacy. You claim solidarity because you went to the fight | To my mind you have got yourself into a mess | You have given your life to show that we are mediocre | You have got stuck while climbing the phallus | It seemed a question of time before you succeeded | They continue to tell you that your mediocrity is temporary | I see you stuck there forever | You will come to envy my nothing | Who said that you do not know power? | “Ich glaube nicht, dass Freakshows etwas Schlechtes sind. Der Freak hat die Macht, er gestaltet die Welt. Er soll sich zeigen.” | To occupy oneself with’ is intellectual arrogance. The more you occupy yourself with women the more estranged you become from me. | Do you know what exposing yourself means? You search for error without being prepared to risk anything | Who said that was self-awareness? That would be a pantomime for fools. It would be over before it even started. | It has become swamped in misunderstandings | It has vanished into stale air | Don’t talk to me if you have ‘experienced self-awareness’. | Self-awareness is the other one | Have you heard about the ‘double militancy’? | And about ‘the private is political’? And the one about ‘you are not doing enough’? | I have found my source of humour. | fin de la performance.

flowRoot.flowPara: Société Réaliste is a Parisian cooperative created by Ferenc Gróf and Jean-Baptiste Naudy in June 2004. It works with political design, experimental economy, territorial ergonomy and social engineering consulting. Polytechnic, it develops its production schemes through exhibitions, publications and conferences.
